/montana/lewis and clark/helena/"], "contributor": ["montana historical society; helena, mt"], "date": "1945-09-14", "dates": ["1945-09-14"], "description": ["V oo V THE PEOPLES VOICE C\u00dcWAW I 35 r\u00fcS\u00e0 ft ft ws ft m gf HELENA MONTANA SEPTEMBER 14 1945 Price Five Cents Vol VINo 42 Whats Gers On fliat The sudden end of the war find 07 3 b r the same condition generally speaking as the rest of th\u00e9 A is far as planning for the postwar period is concerned nothing has been done to meet the problems of providing op portunities for returning war workers and service men and women to reestablish themselves here where they formerly lived n Practically As I have said the same is largely true of conditions in other states But if we are to judge by recent press reports of expressions by socalled leaders nothing will be done in the future in Montana These misnamed leaders apparently want to lull us into a state of complacency into believing that everything is rosy here and there is no call for action In a recent speech Senator Wheeler is reported to have called attention to the fortunate circumstance that Montana is not an industrialized state that it has no problems of re and inferred clearly enough that there is ample the farms of"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-07-03T13:45:49.035Z", "group": ["ndnp/mthi", "montana-historical-society-helena-mt-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86075189/1945-09-14/ed-1/?sp=1", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mthi:batch_mthi_douglasfir_ver01:data:sn86075189:0041421101A:1945091401:0336/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=442&w=338", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mthi:batch_mthi_douglasfir_ver01:data:sn86075189:0041421101A:1945091401:0336/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=884&w=677", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/mthi/batch_mthi_douglasfir_ver01/data/sn86075189/0041421101A/194